abstract: Donald Trump became the third U.S. president to be impeached as the House of Representatives formally charged him on Wednesday with abuse of power and obstructing Congress.
snippet: Donald Trump became the third U.S. president to be impeached as the House of Representatives formally charged him on Wednesday with abuse of power and obstructing Congress.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Donald Trump became the third U.S. president to be impeached as the House of Representatives formally charged him on Wednesday with abuse of power and obstructing Congress.
headline_main: Instant View: Donald Trump Becomes Third U.S. President to Be Impeached
headline_print_headline: Instant View: Donald Trump Becomes Third U.S. President to Be Impeached

abstract: The White House said on Wednesday it was confident the U.S. Senate would exonerate President Donald Trump in a trial after the House of Representatives voted to impeach him for abusing his power and obstructing Congress.
snippet: The White House said on Wednesday it was confident the U.S. Senate would exonerate President Donald Trump in a trial after the House of Representatives voted to impeach him for abusing his power and obstructing Congress.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House said on Wednesday it was confident the U.S. Senate would exonerate President Donald Trump in a trial after the House of Representatives voted to impeach him for abusing his power and obstructing Congress.
headline_main: White House Says It Is Confident Senate Will Exonerate Trump After Impeachment
headline_print_headline: White House Says It Is Confident Senate Will Exonerate Trump After Impeachment

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives passed the second of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting that Trump obstructed Congress by refusing to cooperate with a Democratic-led impeachment investigation.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives passed the second of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting that Trump obstructed Congress by refusing to cooperate with a Democratic-led impeachment investigation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives passed the second of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting that Trump obstructed Congress by refusing to cooperate with a Democratic-led impeachment investigation.
headline_main: U.S. House Votes to Impeach Trump for Obstruction of Congress
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Votes to Impeach Trump for Obstruction of Congress

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives approved the first of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting almost entirely along party lines that he had abused his power by pressuring Ukraine to investigate a political rival.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives approved the first of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting almost entirely along party lines that he had abused his power by pressuring Ukraine to investigate a political rival.
headline_main: U.S. House Votes to Impeach Trump for Abuse of Power
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Votes to Impeach Trump for Abuse of Power

abstract: The impeachment battles over Andrew Johnson, Richard M. Nixon and Bill Clinton came at turning points in the American story. The time that produced President Trump has proved to be another one.
snippet: The impeachment battles over Andrew Johnson, Richard M. Nixon and Bill Clinton came at turning points in the American story. The time that produced President Trump has proved to be another one.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For the most unpredictable of presidents, it was the most predictable of outcomes. Is anyone really surprised that President Trump was impeached? His defiant disregard for red lines arguably made him an impeachment waiting to happen.

abstract: Already comfortable as an outlier in her party, Democratic presidential candidate Tulsi Gabbard did not support the impeachment of President Donald Trump, voting “present” Wednesday on two articles that cleared the House.

abstract: Three lawmakers — Republican Reps. John Shimkus of Illinois and Duncan Hunter of California and Democratic Rep. Jose Serrano of New York — missed the historic House votes to impeach President Donald Trump.
snippet: Three lawmakers — Republican Reps. John Shimkus of Illinois and Duncan Hunter of California and Democratic Rep. Jose Serrano of New York — missed the historic House votes to impeach President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Three lawmakers — Republican Reps. John Shimkus of Illinois and Duncan Hunter of California and Democratic Rep. Jose Serrano of New York — missed the historic House votes to impeach President Donald Trump.

abstract: The nation's top television networks had the patience to follow the House debate on impeaching President Donald Trump on Wednesday — but only to a point.
snippet: The nation's top television networks had the patience to follow the House debate on impeaching President Donald Trump on Wednesday — but only to a point.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The nation's top television networks had the patience to follow the House debate on impeaching President Donald Trump on Wednesday — but only to a point.
headline_main: Networks Stick With Impeachment Drama — to a Point
headline_print_headline: Networks Stick With Impeachment Drama — to a Point

abstract: The president’s favored poem, “The Snake,” isn’t about immigrants. It’s about him.
snippet: The president’s favored poem, “The Snake,” isn’t about immigrants. It’s about him.
lead_paragraph: Dating back to his days on the campaign trail, President Trump has often recited a poem called “The Snake,” as a warning about the dangers of welcoming refugees and immigrants into the country. In the Video Op-Ed above, I show how the parable is much more instructive when applied to Trump’s political rise. From his racist birther conspiracy theory to being forced to pay $2 million for using his charity for his own political gain, anyone paying close attention knew the kind of president he would be.
